Transformations for CRM Analytics Dataflows

append Transformation

A transformation refers to the manipulation of data. You can add transformations to a dataflow to extract data from Salesforce objects or datasets, transform datasets that contain Salesforce or external data, and register datasets.

append Transformation: combines rows from multiple datasets into a single dataset.
augment Transformation: adds columns to a dataset from another related dataset.
computeExpression Transformation: enables you to add derived fields to a dataset using SAQL expressions.
computeRelative Transformation: analyzes trends in your data by adding derived fields based on values in other rows.
delta Transformation: calculates changes in the value of a measure (number) column over time.

digest Transformation: extracts synced connected data in a dataflow.
dim2mea Transformation: creates a new measure based on a dimension.
edgemart Transformation: gives the dataflow access to an existing registered dataset.
export Transformation: creates a data file and schema file from data in a specified source node.
filter Transformation: removes records from an existing dataset based on a filter condition.
flatten Transformation: flattens hierarchical data.

prediction Transformation: produces an Einstein Discovery prediction for a dataset.
sfdcDigest Transformation: generates a dataset based on data extracted from a Salesforce object.
sfdcRegister Transformation: registers a dataset to make it available for queries.
sliceDataset Transformation: removes fields from a dataset in your dataflow.
update Transformation: updates the specified field values in an existing dataset based on data from another dataset.

Overriding Metadata Generated by a Transformation

You can override metadata generated by a transformation. This includes overriding object and field attributes.
